     * [102]N
       Depends on the cause of the coma. Coma can be due to electrolyte
       disturbances, brain injury, stroke, seizures, drug overdose etc.
       The cause needs to be treated and in some cases the coma may be
       reversed. While the patient is comatose they require complete care
       as they cannot do anything for themselves. They will be on a
       ventilator to help them breath, a tube in the stomach for feedings,
       a catheter for urine, constant nursing care for positioning to
       prevent bed sores and muscle contractures.
       Source(s): PA surgical / trauma critical care
